Data Cleaning

library(dplyr)

disney2 <- disney |>
  mutate(genre = factor(genre), 
         rating = factor(MPAA_rating, levels = c("G", "PG", "PG-13", "R")), 
         gross = parse_number(inflation_adjusted_gross),
         release_date = as.Date(release_date, format = "%b %d, %Y"),
         release_year = as.numeric(format(release_date, "%Y")),
         gross_million = round(gross/1000000, digits = 1),
         gross_K = round(gross/1000, digits =3)) |>
  select(-total_gross, -inflation_adjusted_gross, -MPAA_rating ) |>
  drop_na()

Ratings

disney2 |>
  group_by(rating) |>
  summarize(n = n()) |>
  ggplot(aes(x = reorder(rating, -n), y = n)) + 
  geom_col() + ggtitle("Top ratings")

Genres

disney2 |>
  select(genre) |>
  group_by(genre) |>
  summarise(n = n()) |>
  ggplot(aes(x = reorder(genre, n), y = n)) + 
  geom_col() +  coord_flip() + ggtitle("Top genres")

Years

disney2 |>
  select(release_year) |>
  group_by(release_year) |>
  summarise(n = n()) |>
  ggplot(aes(x = release_year, y = n)) + 
  geom_col() + coord_flip() + ggtitle("Movie Count Per Year")

Top Grossing Movies

disney2 |>
  ungroup() |>
  mutate(movie_title = reorder(movie_title, desc(gross_million))) |>
  head(10)  |>
  ggplot(aes(x = reorder(movie_title, gross_million), y = gross_million)) + 
  geom_col(aes(fill = genre)) + coord_flip() + ggtitle("Top Grossing Movies (Millions of Dollars)")

Bottom Grossing Movies

disney2 |>
  ungroup() |>
  arrange(movie_title = reorder(movie_title, gross)) |>
  head(10)  |>
  ggplot(aes(x = reorder(movie_title, -gross), y = gross)) + 
  geom_col(aes(fill = genre)) + coord_flip() + ggtitle("Bottom Grossing Movies (Millions of Dollars)")

Questions

Does release year predict gross revenue?

Plot the model

disney2 |>
  mutate(release_year = as.numeric(release_year)) |>
  ggplot(aes(x = release_year, y = gross_K)) +
  geom_point() + 
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", se = FALSE, color = "blue")
## `geom_smooth()` using formula = 'y ~ x'

Choose a subset to analyze by year

disney3 <- disney2 |>
  filter(release_year >= 1990) |>
  mutate(release_year = as.numeric(release_year))
ggplot(disney3, aes(x = release_year, y = gross_million)) +
  geom_point(shape = 21, colour = 'black', fill = 'white') +
  labs(x = 'Release Year', y = '$ Gross Million') +
  geom_smooth(method='lm', se=FALSE, aes(color = genre)) +
  ggtitle('$ Gross Million vs Release Year') +
  theme_bw()
## `geom_smooth()` using formula = 'y ~ x'

Further subset the data for genre

genres = c("Action", "Adventure")
disney4 <- disney3 |>
  filter(genre %in% genres )
ggplot(disney4, aes(x = release_year, y = gross_million)) +
  geom_point(shape = 21, aes(colour = genre), fill = 'white') +
  labs(x = 'Release Year', y = '$ Gross Million') +
  geom_smooth(method='lm', se=FALSE, aes(color = genre)) +
  ggtitle('$ Gross Million vs Release Year') +
  theme_bw()
## `geom_smooth()` using formula = 'y ~ x'

mod <- disney2 |>
  lm(formula = gross ~ release_year + genre + rating)
